'''MYA''' is an [[acronym]] used by [[geologist]]s and [[paleontologist]]s for "Million Years Ago". 

The [[Burmese language]] ([[ISO 639]] alpha-3, '''mya''')

== Similar abbreviations ==

* TYA: Thousand years ago
* BYA: [[Billion]] Years Ago (10<sup>9</sup> years)<sup>1</sup>
* kYA: [[kilo]]Years Ago (1 kY = 1,000 years)
* GYA: [[Giga]]Years Ago (1 GY = 10<sup>9</sup> years)

The proper [[SI]] units for these are the kiloyear ('''ka''') and gigayear ('''Ga''').

<sup>1</sup> BYA uses the [[short scale]] billion (10<sup>9</sup>), not the [[long scale]] billion (10<sup>12</sup>). This potential for confusion makes it less universal than GYA.

